  "informal_statement": "Let alpha be linearly ordered and beta preordered. If f : alpha -> beta is strictly monotone (a < b implies f a < f b), then f is injective.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Given f a = f b, compare a and b by trichotomy: if a < b then strict monotonicity gives f a < f b, contradicting f a = f b; symmetrically if b < a; so a = b is the only remaining case.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem strictMono_injective {α β : Type*} [LinearOrder α] [Preorder β] (f : α → β) : StrictMono f → Function.Injective f",
